column5: I tried fishing it on my fishing canoe, launched at Queensville sideroad and it was beautiful for boating but the fish were not biting so much.   Anybody know the reason for the lack of fish? There seemed to be tons of excellent fish habitat... Where did the fish go?
sure you don't mean the holland river
Thats what I was thinking as well
What were you fishing for? I fish the holland sometimes
In the past I have caught many perch, crappie, pike, carp and catfish there.

Maybe it was the holland river, but I thought I was starting at Makinonge park. Apparently it connects with the holland in Bradford. So b ause I didn't go downstream all the way I think I was in the more polluted  part. There were othe people there equally unsuccessful
